  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this work is to create a three-dimensional (3D) finite element model (FEM) of the
      human posterior membranous labyrinth, based on in vivo inner ear magnetic resonance imaging
      (MRI). This model has a pedagogical interest, and can serve as a basis for reflection in
      cases of atypical benign paroxysmal positional vertigos. It can also serve for mechanical
      studies of vestibular physiology.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
